to the editor you are right to point out that while bioterrorism is unlikely our ability to respond to a crisis will depend critically upon our existing public health network editorial sept 26 the deadly drug resistant tuberculosis outbreak in new york in the early 1990 's was arrested only after the largely dismantled public health infrastructure was re established we need to learn from that lesson and continue to build our medical and public health resources so that we can respond to any widespread health emergency david s perlin new york sept 26 2001 the writer is scientific director public health research institute

